        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 3:02PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 302 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pinon, or 8 miles northwest of Pueblo Airport, moving southeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pinon and Pueblo Depot.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
